%% Parser Lifecycle & Normalization — how one BaseParser subclass turns raw
%% bytes into a confidence-scored NormalizedEvidence, and how the framework
%% never lets a single artifact crash ingestion or silently lose data
%% (constitution §1.7; docs/adr/0011-evidence-ingestion-pipeline-shape.md).
%% Render with `mmdc -i parser-lifecycle.mmd -o parser-lifecycle.png`.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Registered: registry.register(parser, aliases, priority, enabled)
    Registered --> Selected: factory.select_parser() [declared_type > extension > content sniff]
    Selected --> Decoding: BaseParser.__call__ decodes bytes (detect_encoding)
    Decoding --> Validating: validate_content(raw, decoded_text)

    Validating --> Parsing: content is structurally valid
    Validating --> Degraded: MalformedEvidenceError raised

    Parsing --> Parsed: parse_content() returns NormalizedEvidence
    Parsing --> Degraded: MalformedEvidenceError raised mid-parse

    Degraded --> [*]: confidence=0.0, whole artifact preserved\nin unparsed_fragments (never dropped)
    Parsed --> [*]: confidence in (0.0, 1.0], records + any\nunparsed_fragments returned together

    note right of Selected
        Registered but disabled parsers are
        never selected (registry.disable()).
        A tie between equal-priority candidates
        is broken by each parser's own sniff()
        confidence (core.parsers.factory).
    end note

    note right of Degraded
        This is the ONLY path a parser-level
        exception takes. UnsupportedFormatError /
        ParserValidationError (upload-boundary
        failures) happen before this diagram even
        starts — see evidence-ingestion-pipeline.mmd.
    end note
